🔷 WHAT IS MACHINE LEARNING (IN ONE LINE)

Machine Learning = Teaching machines to learn patterns from data and make decisions without explicitly writing rules.

Example:

Rule-based: if salary > X then approve loan

ML-based: Learn from past approved/rejected loans → predict future loans

🔷 TYPES OF MACHINE LEARNING (CORE FOUNDATION)
1️⃣ Supervised Learning

👉 Data has input + correct output (label)

Problem	Example	Algorithms
Regression	House price	Linear Regression
Classification	Spam / Not Spam	Logistic Regression

Real-world usage

Fraud detection

Disease prediction

Salary prediction

2️⃣ Unsupervised Learning

👉 Data has no labels

Task	Example	Algorithms
Clustering	Customer groups	K-Means
Dimensionality Reduction	Compress features	PCA

Real-world usage

Customer segmentation

Recommendation systems

3️⃣ Semi-Supervised Learning

👉 Few labeled + many unlabeled data
Used when labeling is expensive

4️⃣ Reinforcement Learning

👉 Agent learns by reward & punishment

Example:

Games (Chess, Go)

Robotics

Self-driving cars

🔷 MACHINE LEARNING PIPELINE (INTERVIEW FAVORITE)
Problem → Data → Cleaning → EDA → Feature Engineering
→ Model Selection → Training → Evaluation → Tuning → Deployment

You MUST explain this flow clearly in interviews.

🔷 DATA (MOST IMPORTANT PART – 70% ML)
Types of Data

Numerical (age, salary)

Categorical (gender, city)

Ordinal (rating: low, medium, high)

Text, Image, Time-Series

Data Cleaning Techniques
Problem	Solution
Missing values	Mean / Median / Mode
Outliers	IQR / Z-score
Categorical data	One-Hot Encoding
Scale difference	Standardization
Feature Engineering (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 Converting raw data into useful signals

Examples:

Date → day, month, year

Salary → salary per year

Text → TF-IDF

Interview line:

“Good features matter more than complex models.”

🔷 EXPLORATORY DATA ANALYSIS (EDA)

Purpose:

Understand data

Detect patterns

Find correlations

Techniques:

Mean, median, variance

Histogram

Boxplot

Correlation matrix

🔷 SUPERVISED LEARNING (DEEP DIVE)
🔹 Linear Regression

Used for continuous output

Formula:

y = mx + c

Loss Function:

Mean Squared Error (MSE)

Used in:

House price prediction

Revenue forecasting

🔹 Logistic Regression

Used for classification (YES / NO)

Uses:

Sigmoid function

Outputs probability (0 to 1)

Used in:

Spam detection

Disease prediction

🔹 K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)

👉 Prediction based on nearest neighbors

Problems:

Slow for large data

Sensitive to scaling

🔹 Decision Tree

👉 Rule-based splitting

Pros:

Easy to explain

Handles non-linearity

Cons:

Overfitting

🔹 Random Forest

👉 Multiple decision trees combined

Pros:

Less overfitting

High accuracy

Used in:

Credit scoring

Fraud detection

🔹 Support Vector Machine (SVM)

👉 Finds best boundary (margin)

Used in:

Image classification

Text classification

🔷 UNSUPERVISED LEARNING (DEEP DIVE)
🔹 K-Means Clustering

Steps:

Choose K

Assign points

Update centroids

Repeat

Used in:

Customer segmentation

🔹 PCA (Principal Component Analysis)

👉 Reduce dimensions while keeping variance

Used in:

Image compression

Speeding up models

